node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ricardo Ramos on August 11, 2021. May be an anime-style image of text that says 'GOD WILL FIX YOU @Jesus_The_Lord_'.

node.text: God can mend what is broken in you and turn you into a beautiful masterpiece! But first, you must give Him all the pieces! Take your hurts and your wounds and share them all with God. He is an excellent listener, and He will comfort and strengthen you in the process. In fact, did you know that brokenness is God’s requirement for maximum usefulness? The tests of your life will become your testimony. And I assure you, that there’s someone out there that you could bless by sharing your testimony with them. People would rather hear advice from someone who has been where they are at than from someone who has not been through something similar. God promises to be close to the brokenhearted and will bind up their wounds. So if you are in need of healing, let God fix you! God carefully knit you together in your mother’s womb before you were born, so He can most certainly take your brokenness and make you beautiful. ❤️

node.text:
The biggest and most important decision you will EVER make in your life is whether or not to accept Jesus Christ as your personal Lord and Savior! Jesus came to earth and died on the cross for your sins and mine so that we would be forgiven and made right with God. Jesus arose from the dead on the third day and is now seated at the right hand of God in heaven! Jesus offers you the free gift of eternal life in heaven if you will accept Him into your heart and into your life. I’m asking you to search your heart right now. Are you willing to pray this simple prayer and open your heart and accept Him tonight? I’m praying that your answer is YES. 🙏🏼❤️

If you do decide to accept Jesus on this post, please comment YES I DID in the comments section so that we could rejoice with you and your decision! 🙌🏼❤️🎉🎈🎊

Dear Lord, 
I admit that I am a sinner. I have done many things that don’t please you. I have lived my life for myself only. I am sorry, and I repent and turn from my sins. I ask you to forgive me. 
I believe that you died on the cross for me, to save me. You did what I could not do for myself. I come to you now and ask you to take control of my life; I give it to you. From this day forward, help me to live every day for you and in a way that pleases you. 
I love you, Lord, and I thank you that I will spend all eternity with you. 
Amen. ❤️

node.text:
Do you want to know the best way to fight your battles? It is on your knees in prayer! And Jesus will meet you there. With Jesus on your side, the battle shall be won! Let Him comfort you and guide you in the way that you should go. He will never lead you wrong. So stop worrying and start praying! Jesus will walk with you through the storm every step of the way. And sometimes, Jesus will fight your battles for you and all He requires is for you to be still. Jesus is waiting. Go meet Him. ❤️

“When you go through deep waters, I WILL BE WITH YOU. When you go through rivers of difficulty, you will not drown. When you walk through the fire of oppression, you will not be burned up; the flames will not consume you. (Isaiah 43:2; emphasis mine) 🌟

“The LORD will fight for you; you need only to be still.” (Exodus 14:14) ❤️

“Be still and know that I am God.” (Psalm 46:10) 🌟

node.text: I can honestly say that I have felt every one of these things at one time or another in my life. And for every one of them, Jesus says the exact opposite! Oh, how He loves us! You have been set apart and chosen by our One, True King! And I want you to realize this. We are in this world, not of it. We are just traveling through, trying to reach the hurting and the lost and lead them to Jesus. Heaven is our true destination. And once we get to heaven, there will be no more tears, no more pain, or suffering. And we will be home forever. ❤️

node.text: Jesus loves you so much that He came to earth and died on the cross for your sins and mine so that we would be made right with God and our sins would be forgiven! You are SO totally worth it! Jesus then arose from the dead three days later and He is now seated at the right hand of God in heaven. The biggest and most important decision you will EVER make in your life is this one-whether or not to accept Jesus Christ as your personal Lord and Savior from this day forward! My dear friends, I want you to search your heart right now. Are you ready to pray this simple prayer and ask Jesus to come into your heart and life and be your personal Lord and Savior from this day forward? I want you to realize that we are not promised tomorrow, the next five minutes, or even our next breath! I’m praying for you, and I pray that your answer is YES! 🙏🏼❤️
